 Ms Ashleigh van Rooyen says Mr Matlala deserves a medal for bravery, adding that Middelburg needs more men like him to curb the wave of crime in the CBD.
Ms Van Rooyen visited Shoprite with her mom Hazel around 14:00 on Thursday. While mom Hazel remained in the shop, Ms Van Rooyen left with the trolley full of groceries to load the bags in the car.
As soon as she exited two men accosted her, spurring Mr Matlala to intervene. Also read: Two perish after truck jack-knifes “The robbers were pushing me around but before they could inflict any damage, Mr Matlala was on top of them, fighting them off me,” Ms Van Rooyen says.
One of the robbers immediately fled while his accomplice was locked in a wrestling match with Mr Matlala. Mr Matlala succeeded in dragging the robber into Avbob but before he could lock the security gate, the robber broke loose and made a run for it. Also read: Crime syndicate at large – look out for these men After the attack Mr Matlala assisted Ms Van Rooyen to gather her groceries which was scattered around the car, and loaded the bags into the vehicle. “I want to thank this kind man from the bottom of my heart for his bravery, Mr Matlala you are my hero!” Ms Van Rooyen says.
